  "name": "Flowering Cobra",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span class=\"va-quotation-text\"><em>The coils of the Steel Serpent and the vines of the Intoxicating Petal squeeze the life from all they touch.</em></span></p><p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Two @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.disciplines.Item.iwfbEXyacCnVLEoH]{Intoxicating Petal} maneuvers, two @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.disciplines.Item.HnUsOFIY8vzGre52]{Steel Serpent} maneuvers</p><p><strong>Benefit:</strong> As long as you maintain a Steel Serpent stance, you may treat Intoxicating Petal maneuvers as poison effects when determining how they are affected by your abilities (but not enemy resistances or immunities).</p><p>As long as you maintain an Intoxicating Petal stance, you may treat poisoned creatures and those under the effects of Steel Serpent maneuvers as having [sprout 0].</p>",
